1
00:01:11,559 --> 00:01:12,720
Du Zheng's matter is in the past.

2
00:01:13,279 --> 00:01:14,199
What's wrong?

3
00:01:14,199 --> 00:01:15,440
What's wrong with me today?

4
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:17,160
I have no filter.

5
00:01:17,639 --> 00:01:19,519
I really just want someone to talk to.

6
00:01:20,440 --> 00:01:21,839
How about we go chat in my office?

7
00:01:22,919 --> 00:01:23,480
Jiaqi.

8
00:01:23,839 --> 00:01:25,720
I heard that Du Zheng's case...

9
00:01:26,360 --> 00:01:27,599
...has already been closed, right?

10
00:01:29,599 --> 00:01:31,000
Yes, it's been closed.

11
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:31,760
Hasty.

12
00:01:32,319 --> 00:01:33,160
Too hasty.

13
00:01:33,879 --> 00:01:35,080
The person who hit and killed him...

14
00:01:35,080 --> 00:01:36,480
...is still out there at large.

15
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,480
May lightning strike him.

16
00:01:38,480 --> 00:01:38,959
Section Chief Tan.

17
00:01:39,480 --> 00:01:40,239
I really have to go.

18
00:01:40,239 --> 00:01:40,680
Jiaqi, Jiaqi.

19
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:42,400
Don't, let's chat a bit more.

20
00:01:42,839 --> 00:01:43,559
Lin Jiaqi.

21
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:46,279
What are you doing here instead of working?

22
00:01:47,319 --> 00:01:48,959
Why are you meeting friends at the company?

23
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:50,760
What do you think this place is?

24
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:54,000
Who are you?

25
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:55,559
I am the President of this company.

26
00:01:56,959 --> 00:01:57,760
President.

27
00:01:58,040 --> 00:01:59,120
Didn't you say that before you leave...

28
00:01:59,599 --> 00:02:00,639
...you'd properly hand over your work?

29
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:01,919
Also,

30
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,879
get the business strategy plan ready

31
00:02:03,879 --> 00:02:04,839
and bring it to my office.

32
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:05,919
Right now, immediately.

33
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:07,680
Yes, President.

34
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:11,080
Jiaqi.

35
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:19,960
You two,

36
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:23,600
if you ever dare to take Lin Jiaqi away like this again,

37
00:02:25,039 --> 00:02:26,279
I won't let you off the hook.

38
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,039
The documents you asked for.

39
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:41,759
Why were you with them?

40
00:02:44,919 --> 00:02:46,639
Why can't I be with them?

41
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:50,919
Because it's working hours.

42
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:53,520
Fine.

43
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:55,119
I'm sorry, President.

44
00:03:02,440 --> 00:03:03,160
I just don't like it

45
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:04,160
when you're with Feng Ziang.

46
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,240
And that Section Chief Tan or whatever.

47
00:03:06,839 --> 00:03:07,679
He looks so shady.

48
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:10,000
You can tell by his looks he's no good.

49
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,080
Please don't judge people by their appearance.

50
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:12,199
It's very impolite.

51
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:16,119
I just don't want to see

52
00:03:16,119 --> 00:03:17,360
you with other men.

53
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:20,520
I've already submitted my resignation letter.

54
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:22,399
Even though the handover isn't finished,

55
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:24,520
I'm no longer part of the company.

56
00:03:24,839 --> 00:03:26,360
Who I meet is my own business.

57
00:03:26,759 --> 00:03:28,399
As my boss, you have no right to interfere.

58
00:03:28,759 --> 00:03:29,160
Besides,

59
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:31,279
we no longer have a working relationship.

60
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:33,080
Do you have to be so harsh?

61
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:34,479
When I handed in my resignation yesterday,

62
00:03:34,839 --> 00:03:35,800
it meant I didn't want to have

63
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,160
any personal contact with you anymore.

64
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:39,520
Didn't you say we should take it slow?

65
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:41,360
Then let me tell you clearly.

66
00:03:42,479 --> 00:03:43,479
From beginning to end,

67
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:44,639
we only had an employer

68
00:03:44,639 --> 00:03:46,000
and employee relationship.

69
00:03:46,559 --> 00:03:47,320
But now,

70
00:03:47,639 --> 00:03:49,119
even that relationship is gone.

71
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,199
We won't be developing any further.

72
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:53,639
Also,

73
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:55,839
I've already packed my things.

74
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,160
I'll leave tomorrow after the handover.

75
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,399
If there's nothing else,

76
00:04:01,279 --> 00:04:02,039
I'll get back to work.

77
00:04:09,839 --> 00:04:10,720
Lin Jiaqi, wait.

78
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:13,919
I've made myself very clear.

79
00:04:14,399 --> 00:04:15,960
How else do I have to say it for you to understand?

80
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:17,559
You're the only one allowed to talk and leave?

81
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:19,200
I'm not allowed to speak, is that it?

82
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:20,399
Look at me.

83
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:22,000
Look at my dark circles.

84
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,239
Do you know I haven't slept for nights?

85
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:26,519
Then go to bed early.

86
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,160
Wait.

87
00:04:29,079 --> 00:04:29,839
I want to sleep.

88
00:04:30,079 --> 00:04:31,079
But I have to be able to fall asleep.

89
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:32,440
I just can't figure it out.

90
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:33,799
You clearly said you liked me yesterday.

91
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,160
Why don't you like me today?

92
00:04:36,399 --> 00:04:37,959
Why did you suddenly resign out of nowhere?

93
00:04:38,559 --> 00:04:39,959
If you don't explain this clearly to me,

94
00:04:40,279 --> 00:04:41,200
I'll keep pestering you.

95
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:42,519
Even if you think I'm childish.

96
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:44,200
Unless you make it clear to me.

97
00:04:44,359 --> 00:04:45,559
Why do I have to convince you?

98
00:04:46,079 --> 00:04:47,359
I just don't like you anymore.

99
00:04:47,359 --> 00:04:48,359
There aren't that many reasons why.

100
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:49,119
Also,

101
00:04:49,519 --> 00:04:50,640
it's like orbiting.

102
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:52,160
The Earth revolves around the sun.

103
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:54,000
But the Earth and the sun

104
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,200
are not on the same orbit.

105
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,239
They can never get close.

106
00:04:56,799 --> 00:04:58,239
Just like the relationship between us.

107
00:04:58,679 --> 00:04:59,640
We can't be together.

108
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:02,880
You don't mean that.

109
00:05:04,119 --> 00:05:05,440
If you really meant it,

110
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:07,000
why don't you dare look me in the eye?

111
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:08,040
If you have the guts,

112
00:05:08,359 --> 00:05:09,679
look me in the eye and say it again.

113
00:05:17,359 --> 00:05:18,239
I mean it.

114
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:21,799
I don't like you anymore.

115
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:23,720
I don't want to be with you anymore.

116
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:25,079
There is no reason why.

117
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:26,679
It's that simple.

118
00:05:31,239 --> 00:05:33,040
Why say you like me and then suddenly not?

119
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:34,839
Lin Jiaqi!

120
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:37,959
What exactly do you want?

121
00:05:38,239 --> 00:05:38,839
Are you crazy?

122
00:05:38,839 --> 00:05:39,720
I am crazy.

123
00:05:41,679 --> 00:05:42,880
Haven't you been hiding from me everywhere?

124
00:05:43,239 --> 00:05:44,359
Deliberately ignoring my calls?

125
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:45,720
I didn't want to do this either.

126
00:05:46,279 --> 00:05:47,519
You drove me crazy.

127
00:05:48,799 --> 00:05:49,359
What?

128
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:51,000
You want to kill us both?

129
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:51,559
Yes.

130
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:53,839
My wife is dying soon.

131
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:56,079
Didn't you promise to find a kidney for my wife?

132
00:05:56,359 --> 00:05:57,920
There's been no news at all until now.

133
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:58,760
Let me tell you,

134
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:00,000
if my wife dies,

135
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:02,079
I'll take your life to pay for hers.

136
00:06:02,399 --> 00:06:03,559
How many times have I told you?

137
00:06:04,119 --> 00:06:05,760
Is finding a kidney something I can decide?

138
00:06:06,119 --> 00:06:07,279
Doesn't finding a kidney take time?

139
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:09,679
You just keep stringing me along.

140
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:11,600
Let me tell you,

141
00:06:11,959 --> 00:06:13,959
what I did today is just a reminder.

142
00:06:14,119 --> 00:06:14,839
Next time,

143
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:16,920
we won't be sitting here drinking and chatting.

144
00:06:20,119 --> 00:06:20,959
I'm warning you.

145
00:06:21,519 --> 00:06:22,880
If you dare tell Lin Jiaqi,

146
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:24,320
I won't let you get away with it.

147
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:26,119
Now you're thinking of Lin Jiaqi, huh?

148
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:28,200
When you hit her fiancé back then,

149
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,040
what were you doing?

150
00:06:29,359 --> 00:06:30,040
Let me tell you,

151
00:06:30,279 --> 00:06:31,359
I'm not as much of a jerk as you.

152
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:33,920
I will tell her the whole truth.

153
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:34,880
What did you say?

154
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:37,279
I'll show her the dash cam.

155
00:06:37,279 --> 00:06:38,359
I want her to see

156
00:06:38,359 --> 00:06:39,959
how, right before her fiancé died,

157
00:06:39,959 --> 00:06:41,279
you, as his best friend,

158
00:06:41,279 --> 00:06:42,720
stopped me from saving him.

159
00:06:44,119 --> 00:06:44,880
Don't push me.

160
00:06:45,079 --> 00:06:45,720
What are you gonna do?

161
00:06:46,079 --> 00:06:47,440
You want to silence me, right?

162
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:48,399
Do it.

163
00:06:48,559 --> 00:06:49,519
Do it!

164
00:06:50,119 --> 00:06:51,040
You don't dare, do you?

165
00:06:51,559 --> 00:06:53,160
I knew this would happen,

166
00:06:53,279 --> 00:06:54,359
which is why I chose this place.

167
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:56,200
Just look at how many security cameras are around.

168
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,399
Don't think I won't touch you just because there are cameras.

169
00:07:04,559 --> 00:07:05,839
You're not the only one who's been pushed to the edge.

170
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:07,559
I've been pushed to the edge too.

171
00:07:07,559 --> 00:07:08,200
How about this?

172
00:07:09,119 --> 00:07:10,720
As long as you get this done,

173
00:07:11,359 --> 00:07:13,320
I promise I'll never bother you again.

174
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,279
Officer Lin.

175
00:07:18,959 --> 00:07:19,799
Oh my god.

176
00:07:19,959 --> 00:07:21,160
Are you striking a pose here?

177
00:07:22,119 --> 00:07:23,320
Why are you acting crazy again?

178
00:07:23,320 --> 00:07:24,480
Do you really think this is your home?

179
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:27,119
I have something to tell you.

180
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:29,839
A very important secret.

181
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:34,519
Are you trying to say that you, Gu Tiancheng,

182
00:07:34,519 --> 00:07:35,920
received Du Zheng's heart?

183
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:37,559
How did you know?

184
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:39,760
Let's talk inside.

185
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:45,279
I'm just going to ask you one thing.

186
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:48,079
All those inexplicable things you kept saying before,

187
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:50,600
was it because of Du Zheng's heart?

188
00:07:54,119 --> 00:07:55,640
What kind of nonsense is this?

189
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:59,279
Ever since I received Du Zheng's heart,

190
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:01,480
I've been having the same dream repeatedly.

191
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:04,119
This dream takes me back to the crime scene.

192
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:06,480
So the phone I told you about before,

193
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:07,160
the watch,

194
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:08,079
and the car,

195
00:08:08,359 --> 00:08:09,519
all came from that dream.

196
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,640
Have you ever heard of using a dream as testimony?

197
00:08:13,679 --> 00:08:14,600
This doesn't make sense.

198
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:15,920
And it's not legal either.

199
00:08:16,959 --> 00:08:18,760
We must have overlooked some detail.

200
00:08:19,279 --> 00:08:19,839
And this detail

201
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:22,160
could very well serve as crucial evidence

202
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:23,279
to accuse Feng Ziang.

203
00:08:24,679 --> 00:08:26,279
Then why didn't you say it before? Why now?

204
00:08:26,559 --> 00:08:27,359
I just remembered.

205
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:28,679
Yesterday,

206
00:08:29,239 --> 00:08:30,559
Tan Feng also came looking for Lin Jiaqi.

207
00:08:31,320 --> 00:08:32,280
Tan Feng?

208
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:36,599
The strangest thing is,

209
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,119
he also met with Feng Ziang.

210
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:42,200
So seeing them both

211
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,440
acting so weird at that time,

212
00:08:44,119 --> 00:08:45,039
it's likely that Tan Feng

213
00:08:45,039 --> 00:08:46,719
has something on Feng Ziang.

214
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:48,479
Or it's also possible that

215
00:08:48,799 --> 00:08:50,840
the two of them colluded on the whole thing.

216
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:54,359
Then there is something wrong with these two.

217
00:08:54,919 --> 00:08:56,880
So Officer Lin, we really don't have time.

218
00:08:57,559 --> 00:08:58,919
We all know what kind of person Tan Feng is.

219
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:00,239
I'm afraid he might do something bad

220
00:09:00,239 --> 00:09:01,440
to Jiaqi.

221
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,559
You have to honor your profession.

222
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,080
If you need me,

223
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:08,119
I will help you.

224
00:09:09,039 --> 00:09:10,000
But I'm begging you,

225
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,679
please continue investigating this case, okay?

226
00:09:11,679 --> 00:09:12,280
Look,

227
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:14,239
bro, keep a low profile, okay?

228
00:09:14,239 --> 00:09:15,799
Running to the police station all the time.

229
00:09:16,039 --> 00:09:17,359
Aren't you just asking for trouble?

230
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:19,520
Alright, alright, I get it.

231
00:09:20,479 --> 00:09:21,080
By the way,

232
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:22,919
there's one more thing.

233
00:09:23,520 --> 00:09:24,280
You must promise me.

234
00:09:24,280 --> 00:09:25,799
No, no, no, don't ask me for any favors.

235
00:09:25,799 --> 00:09:27,280
It's definitely nothing good. I won't agree.

236
00:09:27,679 --> 00:09:28,559
What do you mean you won't?

237
00:09:28,719 --> 00:09:29,479
This is an order.

238
00:09:35,599 --> 00:09:36,919
About my heart...

239
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:39,559
Could you keep it from Lin Jiaqi for now?

240
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:42,039
Give me some time.

241
00:09:42,039 --> 00:09:43,239
I'll tell her myself.

242
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:44,760
This matter...

243
00:09:45,559 --> 00:09:47,239
It's better if she hears it from me.

244
00:09:48,679 --> 00:09:49,440
Please.

245
00:09:52,159 --> 00:09:53,000
Alright, I promise you.

246
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:57,320
So when do you plan to tell her?

247
00:10:02,039 --> 00:10:03,039
In a little while.

248
00:10:04,679 --> 00:10:05,919
To say this out loud...

249
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,479
I really need some courage.

250
00:10:13,679 --> 00:10:14,679
President Gu! President Gu!

251
00:10:15,119 --> 00:10:16,119
Something big happened again!

252
00:10:16,679 --> 00:10:17,679
That company in Vietnam...

253
00:10:17,679 --> 00:10:18,479
They went bankrupt!

254
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:20,159
Before they went under,

255
00:10:20,479 --> 00:10:21,919
they actually maliciously

256
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,159
filed for voluntary bankruptcy!

257
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:29,960
Malicious voluntary bankruptcy?

258
00:10:31,599 --> 00:10:32,640
That means...

259
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:34,080
That means

260
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:35,599
apart from getting the initial

261
00:10:35,599 --> 00:10:36,880
20% advance payment,

262
00:10:37,119 --> 00:10:38,479
we'll get nothing else!

263
00:10:39,640 --> 00:10:41,159
Are our 100,000 products still there?

264
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:43,239
Yes, they are!

265
00:10:43,559 --> 00:10:44,520
They're at the port right now.

266
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:45,599
We can recall them anytime.

267
00:10:49,799 --> 00:10:50,479
President!

268
00:10:50,599 --> 00:10:51,559
I just got a call.

269
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:52,960
The creditors and shareholders

270
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:54,119
are arriving at the company soon.

271
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:56,559
They want accountability for the stranded goods.

272
00:11:00,679 --> 00:11:01,359
Gu Tiancheng!

273
00:11:01,599 --> 00:11:02,520
What is going on?

274
00:11:02,919 --> 00:11:04,280
Why are 100,000 new products

275
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:04,919
stranded?

276
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:06,679
It seems our President Gu

277
00:11:06,679 --> 00:11:09,080
didn't properly investigate that Vietnamese company

278
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:10,559
and blindly signed

279
00:11:10,559 --> 00:11:12,880
an export contract for 100,000 products.

280
00:11:14,479 --> 00:11:15,400
It's just a pity

281
00:11:15,679 --> 00:11:17,080
that the company went bankrupt.

282
00:11:17,599 --> 00:11:19,000
What a joke!

283
00:11:19,599 --> 00:11:20,200
Tell us,

284
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:21,479
what should we do next?

285
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:22,640
Do you know how much

286
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:24,239
the stock price has plummeted?

287
00:11:24,719 --> 00:11:25,479
I will try my best...

288
00:11:25,880 --> 00:11:26,679
try my best to find a way.

289
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:27,679
You find a way?

290
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:28,599
I think

291
00:11:28,719 --> 00:11:30,640
you're just trying to stall for time.

292
00:11:31,679 --> 00:11:32,599
As far as I know,

293
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:34,719
stranded goods aren't the only issue.

294
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:37,039
Our President Gu

295
00:11:37,039 --> 00:11:38,239
seems to have pledged shares as collateral

296
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,840
for a loan to produce the new products.

297
00:11:41,599 --> 00:11:42,280
Right?

298
00:11:43,239 --> 00:11:44,000
This explains

299
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,159
why Feimanchi's debts

300
00:11:45,679 --> 00:11:46,520
keep piling up.

301
00:11:47,039 --> 00:11:48,559
And I also heard

302
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:50,960
they're going to start investigating you soon.

303
00:11:52,359 --> 00:11:55,159
Looks like our President Gu needs a break.

304
00:12:00,719 --> 00:12:01,440
Come in.

305
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:04,640
You're just in time.

306
00:12:05,239 --> 00:12:06,320
Explain it to everyone.

307
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:11,119
The freight company just called and said

308
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,559
our goods have arrived at the port

309
00:12:13,559 --> 00:12:14,640
as originally planned.

310
00:12:14,919 --> 00:12:15,520
What?

311
00:12:16,039 --> 00:12:16,799
Arrived at the port?

312
00:12:18,479 --> 00:12:19,280
What do you mean?

313
00:12:20,719 --> 00:12:21,760
It means

314
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,679
our company's 100,000 new products

315
00:12:24,359 --> 00:12:25,679
have been exported as planned.

316
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:27,080
However,

317
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:28,679
they weren't sent to Vietnam,

318
00:12:29,159 --> 00:12:29,960
but to Thailand.

319
00:12:31,039 --> 00:12:31,840
What do you mean?

320
00:12:33,640 --> 00:12:34,599
Didn't you hear clearly?

321
00:12:36,039 --> 00:12:37,280
If you didn't understand,

322
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:39,440
I can explain it to you again.

323
00:12:40,559 --> 00:12:44,000
We didn't produce products for Vietnam.

324
00:12:49,880 --> 00:12:50,679
Dear shareholders,

325
00:12:50,919 --> 00:12:51,679
We

326
00:12:51,679 --> 00:12:53,840
asked our partners in Vietnam

327
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:54,919
to do a little investigation.

328
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:57,359
That so-called Jincheng Company,

329
00:12:57,520 --> 00:12:59,280
its chairman and its external structure

330
00:12:59,359 --> 00:13:00,400
are completely unreliable.

331
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:01,919
So,

332
00:13:02,239 --> 00:13:02,960
we were just lazy,

333
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:04,520
so we didn't produce anything.

334
00:13:05,359 --> 00:13:07,239
But that company actually went bankrupt.

335
00:13:07,640 --> 00:13:08,479
So tell me,

336
00:13:08,919 --> 00:13:09,960
why is my luck

337
00:13:10,719 --> 00:13:11,760
so incredibly good?

338
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,320
Are you kidding me?

339
00:13:17,599 --> 00:13:18,359
Doesn't this mean

340
00:13:18,359 --> 00:13:19,559
we're using Rosenmoss's money

341
00:13:19,559 --> 00:13:20,840
to fund Gu Tiancheng?

342
00:13:22,799 --> 00:13:23,479
I'm sorry.

343
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:24,840
I'm sorry.

344
00:13:25,479 --> 00:13:26,679
What did I say back then?

345
00:13:27,159 --> 00:13:28,799
This matter was highly risky.

346
00:13:28,799 --> 00:13:30,119
Why did you insist on doing it?

347
00:13:30,679 --> 00:13:32,880
Were you just obsessed with ruining Gu Tiancheng,

348
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,840
completely forgetting to protect Rosenmoss's interests?

349
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:36,359
Ruining Gu Tiancheng

350
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,159
is protecting the company's interests.

351
00:13:40,039 --> 00:13:42,440
I think you're just using company resources for personal gain.

352
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:45,760
Why couldn't you

353
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:47,159
just do your own job properly?

354
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:48,239
You just had to do this.

355
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:49,880
What were you trying to prove?

356
00:13:50,679 --> 00:13:52,479
Prove that you're very capable?

357
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:53,599
Great.

358
00:13:53,919 --> 00:13:55,159
I need you to get this straight.

359
00:13:55,159 --> 00:13:56,559
This is all you're capable of.

360
00:13:59,479 --> 00:14:00,400
Next time, I will definitely...

361
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:01,479
Next time?

362
00:14:02,559 --> 00:14:03,880
You're dreaming.

363
00:14:04,239 --> 00:14:05,840
You messed things up like this,

364
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:06,840
do you think Rosenmoss

365
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:08,520
will give you another chance?

366
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:10,039
What do you mean?

367
00:14:11,880 --> 00:14:12,679
Feng Ziang,

368
00:14:13,559 --> 00:14:15,880
let me tell you clearly.

369
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:17,960
What Rosenmoss needs

370
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:19,239
is just a tool.

371
00:14:19,679 --> 00:14:20,679
But as a tool,

372
00:14:20,679 --> 00:14:22,640
you lack even the most basic competence.

373
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:24,400
If it were you,

374
00:14:24,919 --> 00:14:26,159
would you keep it?

375
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,200
Just you wait,

376
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:29,119
Feng Ziang.

377
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:46,960
President Gu, come quickly!

378
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:48,559
Jiaqi is almost done packing her things.

379
00:14:48,559 --> 00:14:49,919
Hurry, hurry, hurry!

380
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:57,119
Why are you so late?

381
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:58,280
How can you make a president

382
00:14:58,280 --> 00:14:59,400
wait downstairs for you for so long?

383
00:15:00,679 --> 00:15:02,799
I had to finish my work before coming over.

384
00:15:03,159 --> 00:15:04,719
Didn't you see me running over here?

385
00:15:05,039 --> 00:15:06,280
You have no conscience.

386
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:08,559
Why is Jiaqi resigning?

387
00:15:09,760 --> 00:15:10,520
Who knows?

388
00:15:11,159 --> 00:15:11,679
Anyway,

389
00:15:12,239 --> 00:15:12,960
she insists on leaving.

390
00:15:13,799 --> 00:15:14,719
Help me think of a way.

391
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:15,719
No matter what,

392
00:15:16,039 --> 00:15:16,840
we can't let her leave.

393
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,359
Is it for the company or for yourself?

394
00:15:20,599 --> 00:15:22,200
I can't help you if you don't make it clear.

395
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:24,280
It's for the company,

396
00:15:25,159 --> 00:15:26,119
and for myself.

397
00:15:26,119 --> 00:15:26,799
Satisfied?

398
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:28,719
Will it work if I persuade her?

399
00:15:28,719 --> 00:15:29,359
It will.

400
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:30,400
She only listens to you in the company.

401
00:15:30,640 --> 00:15:31,119
Let's go.

402
00:15:31,119 --> 00:15:31,599
Really.

403
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:35,039
Break it up, break it up.

404
00:15:35,039 --> 00:15:35,840
Everyone, disperse.

405
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:36,760
Break it up, break it up.

406
00:15:37,119 --> 00:15:38,039
Jiaqi isn't leaving.

407
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:39,000
Come, come, come.

408
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:39,679
Jiaqi.

409
00:15:39,799 --> 00:15:40,520
Break it up.

410
00:15:41,679 --> 00:15:42,440
Uncle Du.

411
00:15:42,919 --> 00:15:44,039
I... I... I...

412
00:15:46,080 --> 00:15:48,159
I heard you're resigning.

413
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:49,280
What's going on?

414
00:15:52,119 --> 00:15:53,440
I've been thinking about it for a while.

415
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:55,840
What are you thinking?

416
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:58,640
The company is finally on the right track.

417
00:15:58,880 --> 00:16:00,280
You've suffered so much before,

418
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:01,840
and now things are finally looking up.

419
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:03,640
Why suddenly think of resigning?

420
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:04,799
E-Exactly.

421
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:07,280
Uncle Du makes sense.

422
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:09,119
About this matter,

423
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:10,880
I'll find time to tell you later.

424
00:16:11,039 --> 00:16:13,919
What are your plans after leaving Feimanchi?

425
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,559
So much has happened in the company recently.

426
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:19,200
I want to rest for a while.

427
00:16:20,919 --> 00:16:22,280
But no matter how long the vacation is,

428
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:23,520
it will eventually end.

429
00:16:23,799 --> 00:16:25,080
What will you do then?

430
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:27,840
I'll figure it out slowly.

431
00:16:28,159 --> 00:16:29,159
I'll take it one step at a time.

432
00:16:29,960 --> 00:16:31,159
But right now,

433
00:16:31,320 --> 00:16:33,520
President Gu hasn't accepted your resignation yet.

434
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:35,599
Why don't you think about it carefully?

435
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:37,440
Yes, yes, yes.

436
00:16:39,599 --> 00:16:40,960
I've thought about it very clearly.

437
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:41,840
Look,

438
00:16:42,039 --> 00:16:43,679
you're doing great in this position.

439
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:45,599
The company is in a critical period right now.

440
00:16:45,799 --> 00:16:46,919
If you hand over your work,

441
00:16:46,919 --> 00:16:48,000
it will delay things.

442
00:16:48,599 --> 00:16:49,919
The key isn't about time.

443
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:51,640
Some people

444
00:16:52,039 --> 00:16:53,159
click the moment they meet.

445
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:55,119
While some people

446
00:16:55,520 --> 00:16:56,960
might never click in a lifetime.

447
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:58,080
This is

448
00:16:58,679 --> 00:16:59,679
destined by fate.

449
00:17:00,080 --> 00:17:00,880
Right.

450
00:17:01,479 --> 00:17:02,320
Jiaqi,

451
00:17:02,520 --> 00:17:04,680
just listen to Uncle Du and don't leave.

452
00:17:05,079 --> 00:17:06,160
We can treat this farewell party

453
00:17:06,520 --> 00:17:07,239
as a

454
00:17:07,239 --> 00:17:08,599
welcome party.

455
00:17:08,959 --> 00:17:10,839
Welcome Uncle Du to visit our company.

456
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:12,040
Good, good, well said.

457
00:17:12,040 --> 00:17:13,119
Welcome party, welcome party.

458
00:17:13,319 --> 00:17:15,359
No, no, I'm not here to visit.

459
00:17:15,359 --> 00:17:17,319
I'm here to persuade Jiaqi not to leave the company.

460
00:17:17,319 --> 00:17:18,400
I... I...

461
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:19,280
I didn't expect this...

462
00:17:27,280 --> 00:17:28,800
Does Rosenmoss have too much free time?

463
00:17:29,719 --> 00:17:31,079
Or do you think our Feimanchi

464
00:17:31,079 --> 00:17:32,000
has been too lucky lately,

465
00:17:32,359 --> 00:17:33,319
and you want to try your luck here?

466
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:34,920
The wheel of fortune turns.

467
00:17:35,479 --> 00:17:36,839
We still don't know who will win in the end.

468
00:17:37,560 --> 00:17:38,680
If that's the case,

469
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:40,680
shouldn't you

470
00:17:41,079 --> 00:17:42,920
go back to your company and keep making trouble?

471
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,199
What are you doing here?

472
00:17:44,719 --> 00:17:45,400
President Gu,

473
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,560
don't you want to have a good chat with me?

474
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:49,439
Haven't we chatted enough?

475
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:52,079
There's never any real progress each time.

476
00:17:53,839 --> 00:17:54,599
You came at the right time.

477
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:56,319
We're having a party.

478
00:17:57,280 --> 00:17:58,839
Speaking of which, we should thank you.

479
00:17:59,479 --> 00:18:01,359
If it weren't for Jincheng International's

480
00:18:01,359 --> 00:18:02,640
portion of the advance payment,

481
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:05,199
our company would have gone bankrupt long ago.

482
00:18:06,079 --> 00:18:07,079
Everyone would have left by now.

483
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:08,199
Alright,

484
00:18:08,359 --> 00:18:09,280
we still have a party to enjoy.

485
00:18:09,479 --> 00:18:10,319
We don't have time for you.

486
00:18:10,319 --> 00:18:10,880
Get out.

487
00:18:18,239 --> 00:18:18,920
Uncle Du,

488
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:22,239
did you know someone investigated

489
00:18:22,239 --> 00:18:23,520
your and Du Zheng's medical information?

490
00:18:23,599 --> 00:18:24,280
Feng Ziang!

491
00:18:24,839 --> 00:18:26,119
Feng Ziang, don't push it too far!

492
00:18:26,719 --> 00:18:28,640
My and Du Zheng's medical information?

493
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:29,880
To be exact,

494
00:18:30,239 --> 00:18:31,560
it's the organ donation form

495
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,400
for Du Zheng that you signed yourself.

496
00:18:34,719 --> 00:18:35,839
Don't you want to know

497
00:18:35,839 --> 00:18:36,520
why this person wanted to

498
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:37,239
investigate this information?

499
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:40,119
This person is right in front of you,

500
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:41,520
this President Gu.

501
00:18:46,439 --> 00:18:47,800
But why did he do it?

502
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:53,760
It's because your son

503
00:18:54,319 --> 00:18:56,280
Du Zheng's heart was transplanted into him.

504
00:18:56,920 --> 00:18:57,599
Stop talking!

505
00:18:57,599 --> 00:18:58,280
Jiaqi!

506
00:18:58,880 --> 00:18:59,719
Don't stop him.

507
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:01,319
Let him speak.

508
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:03,680
Du Zheng's death

509
00:19:04,439 --> 00:19:06,040
allowed the man in front of you to survive.

510
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:08,400
But not only is he ungrateful,

511
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:10,400
he even tried to steal Du Zheng's fiancee.

512
00:19:14,520 --> 00:19:15,239
Gu Tiancheng,

513
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:17,319
haven't you always wanted to know

514
00:19:17,319 --> 00:19:19,400
why Lin Jiaqi can't be by your side?

515
00:19:20,359 --> 00:19:20,880
That's because you

516
00:19:20,880 --> 00:19:23,040
survived in place of the person she loved most.

517
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:25,239
Haven't you always wanted to know

518
00:19:25,239 --> 00:19:26,959
why she insisted on leaving Feimanchi?

519
00:19:27,959 --> 00:19:29,160
Even when Uncle Du tried to persuade her,

520
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:30,079
she still wanted to leave.

521
00:19:30,439 --> 00:19:31,439
I'll tell you right now.

522
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:33,079
Because she doesn't want to see you.

523
00:19:33,439 --> 00:19:35,199
She doesn't want to see her beloved's heart

524
00:19:35,199 --> 00:19:36,800
wrapped in a filthy shell,

525
00:19:37,079 --> 00:19:38,760
and then using this honest and kind heart

526
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:39,959
to do despicable and shameless things.

527
00:19:39,959 --> 00:19:40,800
Stop talking!

528
00:19:45,719 --> 00:19:46,400
Jiaqi!

529
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:48,119
Jiaqi!

530
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:49,719
Jiaqi!

531
00:19:51,359 --> 00:19:52,040
Jiaqi!

532
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:53,079
Gu Tiancheng.

533
00:19:55,319 --> 00:19:55,880
What?

534
00:19:56,439 --> 00:19:57,319
Did I hit a nerve?

535
00:19:58,560 --> 00:19:59,280
Gu Tiancheng,

536
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:01,760
so what if you won this round with Jincheng International?

537
00:20:02,119 --> 00:20:03,199
When it comes to the person you care about most,

538
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:04,880
you've lost completely,

539
00:20:05,760 --> 00:20:07,000
with no chance of a comeback.

540
00:20:15,439 --> 00:20:16,119
Lin Jiaqi.

541
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:17,680
Lin Jiaqi!

542
00:20:20,319 --> 00:20:21,920
Did you already know about this?

543
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:23,959
Yes.

544
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:25,680
I've known for a while.

545
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:27,239
Now you finally understand

546
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:29,520
why I did what I did before, right?

547
00:20:30,199 --> 00:20:31,280
Can we talk?

548
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:32,560
There's nothing to talk about.

549
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:34,760
I'm going home.

550
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:35,719
Lin Jiaqi!

551
00:20:37,040 --> 00:20:38,520
Is me getting Du Zheng's heart

552
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:40,479
really that unacceptable to you?

553
00:20:43,839 --> 00:20:44,599
Yes.

554
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:46,719
It's unacceptable.

555
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:47,920
Why?

556
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:50,359
Am I, Gu Tiancheng,

557
00:20:50,359 --> 00:20:51,400
so unworthy in your eyes?

558
00:20:53,239 --> 00:20:54,400
Then what do you want me to do?

559
00:20:55,599 --> 00:20:57,239
This heart is already inside my body.

560
00:20:58,439 --> 00:20:59,479
Do I have to rip it out

561
00:20:59,479 --> 00:21:00,599
for you to accept it?

562
00:21:07,079 --> 00:21:08,119
You don't have to do anything.

563
00:21:49,719 --> 00:21:50,359
Lin Jiaqi!

564
00:21:51,479 --> 00:21:52,280
Where are you going?

565
00:21:53,599 --> 00:21:54,839
I want to go away for a while.

566
00:21:56,359 --> 00:21:57,520
Do you really not want to see me that badly?

567
00:21:58,800 --> 00:22:00,319
Du Zheng will always be between us.

568
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:06,199
Everything right now

569
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,319
makes me feel so confused.

570
00:22:09,520 --> 00:22:11,560
I can't stop overthinking.

571
00:22:12,040 --> 00:22:13,119
I don't know if our feelings for each other

572
00:22:13,119 --> 00:22:14,400
are because of Du Zheng.

573
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:17,359
Just thinking about it brings me so much pain.

574
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:18,800
So...

575
00:22:20,199 --> 00:22:21,119
let's just forget it.

576
00:22:22,719 --> 00:22:24,000
I understand everything you're saying.

577
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:26,719
But we can try again.

578
00:22:27,719 --> 00:22:28,479
Don't you always say,

579
00:22:29,199 --> 00:22:30,160
if we don't try,

580
00:22:31,119 --> 00:22:32,359
how will we know if it works or not?

581
00:22:35,599 --> 00:22:36,920
We can't try with this.

582
00:22:38,040 --> 00:22:38,760
I'm sorry.

583
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:44,640
But none of this is my fault!

584
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:46,079
Is it wrong that I survived?

585
00:22:46,760 --> 00:22:48,199
Getting Du Zheng's heart

586
00:22:48,599 --> 00:22:49,839
wasn't my choice either!

587
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:52,119
Why is it that because I lived,

588
00:22:52,319 --> 00:22:53,520
I have to lose you?

589
00:22:55,319 --> 00:22:56,400
Lin Jiaqi!
